headlines.description: Jordan Lyons scored 17 points with five 3s, John Davis III added 15 points, and Furman made 16 3-pointers and used a 43-3 run to beat VMI 87-57 in Saturday's Southern Conference opener.
headlines.shortLinkText: Furman hits 16 3s in 87-57 win over VMI

headlines.description: Mike Cunningham scored a season-high 23 points and South Carolina Upstate beat Division II North Greenville 80-59 on Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: SC Upstate beats Div. II North Greenville 80-59

headlines.description: Ahmad Thomas scored 24 points and UNC Asheville held off Campbell for an 85-79 victory Saturday in a Big South opener.
headlines.shortLinkText: Thomas scores 24 in UNC Asheville's 86-79 victory

headlines.description: Xzavier Taylor totaled 12 points and 12 rebounds and Bryson Scott scored 18 to lead Fort Wayne past NAIA Concordia (MI) 92-59 on Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Fort Wayne downs NAIA Concordia (MI) 92-59 behind Taylor

headlines.description: Muhammad-Ali Abdur-Rahkman scored 20 points and Michigan extended its winning streak to a season-high five games with a 76-51 victory over Jacksonville on Saturday.
Austin Luke scored 19 points and dished out 10 assists to help Belmont hold off Tennessee-Martin for a 65-58 win Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Belmont holds off UT-Martin for 65-58 win

headlines.description: Pauly Paulicap scored 16 points and grabbed nine rebounds, Thomas Capuano hit a go-ahead 3, and Manhattan opened its conference schedule by holding off Fairfield 61-58 on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Manhattan holds off Fairfield 61-58 in MAAC opener

headlines.description: Kyle Williams had 16 of his 21 points in the final 6  1/2 minutes on Saturday night and Norfolk State rallied from a 10-point deficit to beat Stony Brook 74-68.
headlines.shortLinkText: Williams rallies Norfolk State over Stony Brook 74-68

headlines.description: Justin Coleman scored a career-high 28 points and distributed six assists and Eric Adams scored 11 points and Samford defeated Chattanooga 73-56 on Saturday night in a Southern Conference opener.
headlines.shortLinkText: Coleman's career night lifts Samford past Chattanooga 73-56

headlines.description: Bryson Robinson scored five of his seven points in the final minutes to give New Orleans enough of an advantage to hold off Houston Baptist 64-57 on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: New Orleans scrambles to beat Houston Baptist 64-57

headlines.description: Kenneth Ogbe scored 23 points including a key 3-pointer and Utah Valley beat Cal State Fullerton 87-78 on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Utah Valley makes 30 FTs, beats Cal State Fullerton 87-78

headlines.description: Colton Weisbrod scored 26 points and grabbed 14 rebounds and Josh Nzeakor scored 17 with 11 rebounds and Lamar beat Texas A&M Corpus Christi 77-72 on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Garth comes up clutch for Lamar over Texas A&M-CC 77-72

headlines.description: Jared Stutzman had 17 points and Brandon Boyd scored 15 to help Idaho State beat Weber State 62-60 on Saturday night in the Big Sky Conference opener for both teams.
headlines.shortLinkText: Stutzman, Boyd lead Idaho St. to 62-60 win over Weber St.

nowFeed.headline: Under Sean Miller Deandre Ayton is maximizing his enormous potential. Ayton has always possessed the physical tools and a solid basketball IQ. He has worked hard at Zona along with making the adjustments to college basketball. For a freshman big man it's really hard to dominate right away. Since he arrived in the states he was a top ranked player in his class. Would have been top 5 in last years NBA draft. Now he will be a top 3 pick and will be much more prepared.

nowFeed.headline: Cincinnati's loss at Houston will likely drop them from the No. 2-seed line in Joe Lunardi's Bracketology, with Texas Tech likely being the beneficiary to move up. The Cougars, who were a 10-seed coming into the night, scored another big resume win after picking one up over Wichita State in January.
nowFeed.story: Cincinnati's loss at Houston will likely drop them from the No. 2-seed line in Joe Lunardi's Bracketology, with Texas Tech likely being the beneficiary to move up. The Cougars, who were a 10-seed coming into the night, scored another big resume win after picking one up over Wichita State in January.

nowFeed.headline: Houston upsets No. 5 Cincinnati 67-62, ending the Bearcats nation-leading 16-game winning streak. It's the first time the Cougars have beaten two top-10 opponents in a season since 1984.

nowFeed.headline: Ironically, Cincinnati's loss to Houston also finally gives Cincinnati its first win over a likely NCAA Tournament team.
